overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, aiming to verify its adherence to a detailed specification and
  Statement of Work. The review process involved examining the codebase,
  including types, validations, API endpoints, and UI components, to identify
  any discrepancies or missing features. The resulting plan highlighted several
  critical gaps, such as the absence of a tiredness severity scale with safety
  warnings, COMISA detection, and outbound links in the report. The immediate
  action taken was to implement the 1-10 tiredness severity scale in the
   component, including dynamic safety messaging for high
  severity scores, and updating the corresponding types and validation schema.
  This ensures that the application now captures a more nuanced understanding of
  a user's tiredness and provides crucial safety guidance when necessary.
